org.apache.flex.compiler.definitions

Interface ITypeDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IMemberedDefinition, IScopedDefinition
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IAppliedVectorDefinition, IClassDefinition, IInterfaceDefinition, ITypedClassNode
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AppliedVectorDefinition, ClassDefinition, ClassDefinitionBase, ClassTraitsDefinition, InterfaceDefinition, TypeDefinitionBase

    public interface ITypeDefinition
extends IMemberedDefinition
    The base interface for class and interface definitions, including definitions of vector types.

    • Method Detail

      • isInstanceOf

        boolean isInstanceOf(ITypeDefinition type,
                   ICompilerProject project)
        Determines whether an "is-a" relationship exists between two classes or interfaces.

        If this is an IClassDefinition and type is an IClassDefinition, this method determines whether this is a subclass of type.

        If this is an IClassDefinition and type is an IInterfaceDefinition, this method determines whether this is implements type.

        If this is an IInterfaceDefinition and type is an IInterfaceDefinition, this method determines whether this is a subinterface of type.

        A class or interface is considered an instance of itself.

        Parameters:
        type - An ITypeDefinition representing a class or interface.
        project - The ICompilerProject within which references should be resolved
        Returns:
        A flag indicating whether an "is-a" relationship exists between the two types.

      • isInstanceOf

        boolean isInstanceOf(String qualifiedName,
                   ICompilerProject project)
        A variant of isInstanceOf which takes a fully-qualified type name rather than an ITypeDefinition.

        While not @deprecated, this method may not do what you want because the scope containing this type definition will be used to resolve the name that is specified rather than some other scope which may actually contain the name in source code.

        Parameters:
        qualifiedName - A String, such as "flash.display.Sprite" , that specified a fully-qualified type name.
        project - The ICompilerProject within which references should be resolved
        Returns:
        A flag indicating whether an "is-a" relationship exists between the two types.
